Book - Class in backgroud
Class used for the creation of book objects
Book(String, String, String, ArrayList<String>, int) - Constructor for class backgroud.Book
The constructor of this class takes 5 parameters and sends one to the super class in order initialize a new Book
Borrowable - Class in backgroud
Class is meant to serve as super class for Book and Periodical in order to link them so that they later can live within the same ArrayList in the Library class
Borrowable(String) - Constructor for class backgroud.Borrowable
This constructor is used by the subclass in order to initialize the inherited callNumber field Additionally this constructor sets the default value for the status to true thus making a Borrowable(Book/Periodical) available upon creation
BorrowReturn - Class in frames

BorrowReturn(Library) - Constructor for class frames.BorrowReturn
